 Introduction

The Rocket League® GamePack features Power Mods with Primary & Secondary buttons that allows you to use Front Speedflip, Back Speedflip, Camera Shake Block, Stall, Auto Ballcam Short, Auto Ballcam Long, Speed Drift, Stop-Car, 180 Backflip Shot, Takeoff, Musty Flick, After Drift, Kickoff Speedflip, Breezi Flick, Wavedash, Torandospin, Boost Saver, Fast Flip to any Power button you assign giving you the upper advantage in every match.
Also incorporated are Custom Button assignment for Drive Forwards, Drive Backwards, Jump, Boost, Powersilde, Air Roll, Focus On Ball, Air Roll Right, Air Roll Left.

🛠
 How to Setup this GamePack

There are two methods to setup and configure Mods in this GamePack, the first being the GamePack Configuration Interface (or GCI) and the second is the Zen OLED Menu System.​

​​
⚙
 GamePack Configuration Interface (GCI)

The GCI either pops up every time you program a GamePack to a memory slot, or when you click on the memory slot number in Zen Studio. This is a really quick way to setup all your preferred defaults from the get-go.
GamePack Default Settings: All default values are optimized for console gaming with a controller. If using
🖱
Mouse & keyboard, you should expect to have to change almost all default settings to suit your preferred playing style, in particular changing all in-game stick sensitivity settings to maximum.
It's very important that you setup your mouse before trying to use any GamePacks or scripts.

GCI COMING SOON!

​​
🔲
 Zen OLED Menu System

The Zen OLED Menu System is a new groundbreaking feature that allows the configuration and tuning of dozens of different Mod modes and combinations, on-the-fly and in seconds, all from an easy to read OLED interface. Once you have programmed this GamePack to a memory slot it must be enabled and active. This is done by pressing the Memory Slot Button (P1) until the logo of the GamePack you wish to use appears on the OLED screen.
When you see the logo of this GamePack displayed on the screen, simply hold LT/L2 & press MENU/OPTIONS to access the Mod Menu System.
Community GamePack OLED Menu System Quick Toggle: HOLD LT/L2 & PRESS MENU/OPTIONS
All Adjustable Mods can be tuned and tested in real-time directly from the Zen GamePack OLED Adjustables Menu.

​
♻
 Screensaver

The Zen OLED Menu System has built in screensaver protection to help protect against screen burn. It will kick in after 3 minutes of inactivity. Press any button to return to the Mod Menu screen.
Press Play for Screensaver Demo

​
🕹
 Jump Toggles

Jump Toggles allow you to access the OLED MOD MENU System and instantly select a Power Mod while gaming.
This GamePack reads the input of a controller, if it detects a Playstation controller it will use Touchpad regardless of the platform you play on for the toggle. Otherwise, it uses View or the button that would be in its place such as Minus on a Nintendo Pro controller.
Touchpad is used instead of Share Button because it is easier to press on a Playstation Controller. Compared to the Xbox controller where the View button is next to the left stick. This requires a slight move with your thumb. The intention is to make sure the comfort is the same with a Playstation Controller
Jump Toggle
Action
Hold VIEW/TOCHPAD & Press RB/R1
Power Mod Selection Menu

 Quick Toggles

Quick Toggles allow you to access the OLED Menu System and instantly enable/disable active Mods while gaming.
Note: When a Mod is disabled, any associated Quick Toggle is also disabled.

 In-Game Settings

These are all of the settings required for the Mods to function correctly, and they also allow you to dramatically improve the quality and accuracy of your characters movement.
​

​
 Matching Buttons

Match all Buttons In-Game to the Gamepack Buttons.
This step is critical. If you don't select the same Button Layout Presets that you are using in-game, several Mods in this GamePack will not function correctly.
  1. 1.
    Press the MENU/OPTIONS button on your controller.
  2. 2.
    Press RB/R1 2 times to navigate to CONTROLS.
  3. 3.
    Select VIEW/CHANGE BINDINGS.
  4. 4.
    Match all In-Game Buttons to the GamePack Buttons

 Power Button 1 Primary

Select the Primary activator for the Power 1 Mod. Power Buttons are custom toggles you set to activate Mods. Typically these are preset in GamePacks. Though with there being custom controls and binds settings can vary vastly between users. You are able to set custom ways to activate any given mod. There are up to 4 Power Mods that can be used. You will want to make sure that the Power Buttons used for the toggles do not interfere with your binds. For instance, if the Speed Flip mod was set to activate with a Power Button that is also your Camera button this can cause the camera to focus then unfocus from the ball when activating the mod.
Pro Tip: When selecting a custom Power Button toggle it is recommended to use 2 different buttons. Though, should you choose you can use the same button for a Power Mod. It is possible to set Takeoff to activate on Down Dpad only by making both Power Buttons for Power Mod 2 Down Dpad. In cases such as this, it is recommended to unbind the button you would like to activate a mod.

 In-Game Vibration

This option blocks all rumble signals sent from the game but still allows the GamePack to read in-game rumble frequencies for special Rumble Mode support. In-Game rumble/vibration must still be enabled.
  1. 1.
    Press the MENU/OPTIONS button on your controller.
  2. 2.
    Press RB/R1 2 times to navigate to CONTROLS.
  3. 3.
    Select VIBRATION and set it to ALL.
In-Game Setting: Vibration
#
Option
Text
0
Disabled
Controller WILL receive rumbles
1
Enabled
Controller WILL NOT receive rumbles
​

​
 Power Mod Adjustments

To adjust the timing for the Power Mods Press A/Cross to enter this menu while in-game.
Adjustables for Power Mods:
Safe Boost Ground Time (100 - 3000): This allows you to adjust the time to end boost when on solid ground.
Safe Boost Air Time (500 - 4000): This allows you to adjust the time to end boost while in the Air.
Jump Drift Time (100 - 3000): This allows you to adjust the time to drift after jumping.
Jump Dodge Time (100 - 3000): This allows you to adjust the time to drift after dodging.
Air Roll Time (100 - 2000): This allows you to adjust the time to roll after a jump.
Angle Alignment Time (100 - 2000): This allows you to adjust the time to adjust alignment after a jump.
Camera Focus Time (100 - 3000): This allows you to adjust the time the camera is focused on your car before switching back to the ball.
Speed Drift Strength (1 - 100): This allows you to adjust the effective strength of Speed Drift.
Straight Fly Time (100 - 1500): This allows you to adjust the length of time the first flight lasts.
LY Time (10 - 1500): This sets the length of time the LY Axis is used before a dodge.
LX Time (10 - 1500): This sets the length of time the LX Axis is used before a dodge.
Jump Time (1 - 1000): This allows you to adjust the length of time between the first jump and dodge.
#
Option
Description
0
Press A / Cross to Enter
By pressing A/Cross let you access the Power Mod Adjustments

​
 Power 1 Mod

Power 1 Mod gives you a selection of different mods you can use with the Power Button.
#
Option
Description
0
Disabled
Power Mod & Quick Toggle is Disabled
1
Front Speedflip
Performs perfect diagonal dodges while flipping at maximum speed moving forwards left or right. To activate hold Boost and the left analog stick forwards in a diagonal direction and double tap your In-Game jump Button.
2
Back Speedflip
This mod gives you the fastest way to turn around your car. Simply hold back on the left analog stick for 400ms or more and double tap your iIn-Game Jump Button.
3
Camera Shake Block
While enabled this will prevent your camera from wobbling when using a controller with high stick noise automatically.
4
Stall
This is a trick to provide more air time without sacrificing your position while waiting for a pass
5
Auto Ballcam Short
Return to Ball Came after 800ms after pressing your In-Game Ball Cam Button.
6
Auto Ballcam Long
Return to Ball Came after 10 seconds after pressing your In-Game Ball Cam Button.
7
Speed Drift
Automatically drift while steering. Before activating this mod your left analog stick will need to be deflected 95% forwards or greater to either the left or right.
8
Stop-Car
Stops your car while driving allowing you to reposition easier.
9
180 Backflip Shot
When activated you will jump, turn 180 degrees, perform a half backwards dodge, air roll right then power drift. This is to be performed when balancing the ball on the hood of your car.
10
Takeoff
Instantly takeoff at a 45 degree angle which can be used to defend or take a shot being passed to you.
11
Musty Flick
A musty flick is an abnormal flick where the player jumps, pushes nose down, than backwards dodges to push the ball up in the air. It was invented/popularized by the player Musty.
12
After Drift
This will have your car drift after jumping making certain maneuvers easier. When enabled jump then drive forwards to stop drifting. This should not be used if drift and air roll are bound to the same button.
13
Kickoff Speedflip
Perform a full kickoff while speed flipping. This is to be used right as the countdown ends.
14
Breezi Flick
A Breezi Flick is the perfect way to show off your finesse on the ground and while it might not be the best way to score in any situation and can generate an insane amount of power and look good doing it.
15
Wavedash
Wave Dashing in a maneuver which essentially allows you to cancel a a directional dodge while still accruing all of the forward momentum that the dodge would have given you. In short, this technique allows you to gain the speed of a dodge, but in a quicker time frame and without committing to a directional dodge.
16
Torandospin
A Tornadospin will have you to spin in air and allow you to adjust your car to get a good touch with power
17
Boost Saver
This mod will stop your car from boosting after going supersonic then boost again after your chosen time.
18
Fast Flip
Fast Flip will have a front flip perform a speed flip allowing your car to travel faster when dodging forwards.
Power 1 Mod Quick Toggle: HOLD LT/L2 + PRESS D-PAD UP

🔀
 Crossover Auto-Remap

When this GamePack is being used on a PlayStation 4 or 5 and detects the connected controller is not a DualSense or DualShock 4, it will automatically reassign Touchpad to the Select/Back/View/Minus Button so you are still able to utilize in-game Touchpad functionality on a PlayStation while using a Crossover controller. You can also access the PS5/PS4 Share Screen by pressing Select/Back/View/Minus + RS (Right Stick).
When this GamePack is being used on an Xbox Series X|S and detects the connected controller is not an Xbox Series X|S Controller but a PlayStation controller, it will automatically reassign Share to the Touchpad so you are still able to utilize in-game Share Button functionality on an Xbox Series X|S while using a PlayStation controller.

Troubleshooting

If you are experiencing unstable performance or settings issues with your GamePack, it's likely that the configuration profile has become corrupted. This can sometimes happen when updating to a newer GamePack version with major structural changes, or using a memory slot that already had a pack previously programmed to it.
Simply select Device
👉
 Erase Memory Slots, once finished unplug the Zen mini-USB cable, then go to File
👉
 Relaunch as Admin, reconnect the mini-USB cable to the Zen, and program the GamePack again. You will now find the Mods are working as they should
😃
